\par
Red scleroid and golden iris. This would create a most striking sight capable of powerful vision. Perhaps, following his rebirth, my attacker would see differently, or perhaps he would hate me all the more. Drying my tears, I decided not to return to my pedestal of rock in the middle of the field. Not knowing how to feel or what to make of this strange sequence of events, I thought perhaps a better rock to perch on would be found high atop a mountain peak. My wings carried me swiftly into the air to find such lofty heights.\par
