If you attempt to sell a book which purports to garner lots of interest, change society, yet earns its readers no money--people will hesitate even to borrow it from a library. So to write such a thing, it must be something so radically new it barely attempts to have an impact on society initially at all. If you write a book titled \ldblquote How to Change A Society\rdblquote  it would likely get more than its fair share of interest from people interested in politics. A \ldblquote theoretical church\rdblquote  is the best institutional mimic for this, and has been modeled in the likes of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FDiscordianism&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNED-XYExq4K-KAEah7rwexwmKcl8w"}}{\fldrslt{\cf3\ul Discordianism\cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FDiscordianism&sa=D&sntz=1&usg=AFQjCNED-XYExq4K-KAEah7rwexwmKcl8w"\cf3\ul\v0  }}}\cf1\ulnone\f0\fs22 and the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"}}{\fldrslt{\cf3\ul Church\cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"\cf3\ul\v0  \cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"\cf3\ul\v0 of\cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"\cf3\ul\v0  \cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"\cf3\ul\v0 the\cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"\cf3\ul\v0  \cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"\cf3\ul\v0 Subgenius\cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"\cf3\ul\v0  (\cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"\cf3\ul\v0 Bob\cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_SubGenius"\cf3\ul\v0 ).}}}\cf1\ulnone\f0\fs22  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://atheoreticalchur