\pard\sl276\slmult1\b0\fs22\tab Our earliest models for relationships are those we form with our parents when we first begin transactions with them as other conscious beings. From the moment we learn to smile at our parents in exchange for food we learn the fundamental underlying concept about the universe which bootstraps us into intelligence. The underlying value in this interaction is the understanding that when the infant receives food for smiling it profits from nourishment, its carers profit from the knowledge their child will grow more vigorously, and both parties profit from the activity of smiling. Making good value trades is profitable for everyone.\par
\pard\fi720\sl276\slmult1\par
Lots of babies and children are generally very happy, so happy they enjoy moving around, discovering profitable ways of spending their time. For a child, every action is a new discovery, so much of the time the trade-offs they choose to make can be frustrating. In order to rediscover and test parental responses to behavior, children will be intentionally naughty. Beginning with throwing tantrums, throwing food, making marks on walls. They will also be unintentionally naughty and deliberately cute by repeatedly wiping their nose on their parent. Children do this because they need their values constantly reinforced. Their highly neuroplastic brains receive far more input from their senses which also perceive their world more strongly. Think about the tastes and aromas of food you used to enjoy when you are a child, and now think about what pre-prepared baby food tastes like. For this reason some mothers choose to prepare their child\rquote s food from scratch because doing so prepares them to form eating habits more similar to theirs. This is interesting because teaching intelligent eating habits as early as possible is an excellent way of growing healthier happier children.\par
\pard\sl276\slmult1\par
\pard\fi720\sl276\slmult1 There are some children who move constantly or even headbang (especially when they try to go to sleep). For these people, the repetitive task of sloshing the brain around inside the surface of the skull by banging or shaking the head back and forth repeatedly, feels like a massage for the mind. Doing this more safely was demonstrated in{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0356721/"}}{\fldrslt{ \v HYPERLINK "http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0356721/"\cf3\ul\v0 I\cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0356721/"\cf3\ul\v0  \cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0356721/"\cf3\ul\v0 Heart\cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0356721/"\cf3\ul\v0  \cf1\ulnone\v HYPERLINK "http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0356721/"\cf3\ul\v0 Huckabees}}}\cf1\ulnone\f0\fs22  by people assisting each other to be unsuspectingly hit in the face with balloons. This method was described as pure being and is a \lquote rushing\rquote  or \ldblquote flow\rdblquote  experience of consciousness, albeit one you cannot achieve anything in except experience the rush, or assist another person to experience it.\par
